{"cwd": "/tmp/cch-sandboxes/20260620T170014/webfetch-tool", "duration_ms": 2815, "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "session_id": "<SESSION_ID>", "tool_input": {"prompt": "page title", "url": "https://example.com"}, "tool_name": "WebFetch", "tool_response": {"bytes": 559, "code": 200, "codeText": "OK", "durationMs": 2814, "result": "# Analysis of Example Domain Page\n\nThe page is a simple informational landing page for example.com. \n\nThe main heading states: **\"This domain is for use in documentation examples without needing permission.\"** The content explains that example.com serves as a reserved domain specifically designated for illustrative purposes in technical documentation and tutorials.\n\nThe page encourages visitors to \"Learn more\" via a link to IANA's domain documentation, where additional information about special-use domains is available. The overall message conveys that using this particular domain in examples, guides, and educational materials is both appropriate and permitted—making it a practical resource for developers and technical writers who need a placeholder domain.", "url": "https://example.com"}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_01CUhKVQAQKiaqMNMFtwMoHM", "transcript_path": "<TRANSCRIPT_PATH>"}
