{"cwd": "/tmp/cch-sandboxes/20260620T170014/websearch-tool", "duration_ms": 7766, "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse", "permission_mode": "bypassPermissions", "session_id": "<SESSION_ID>", "tool_input": {"query": "claude code hooks"}, "tool_name": "WebSearch", "tool_response": {"durationSeconds": 7.765353661000001, "query": "claude code hooks", "results": [{"content": [{"title": "Automate actions with hooks - Claude Code Docs", "url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks-guide"}, {"title": "GitHub - disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery: Master Claude Code Hooks · GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/disler/claude-code-hooks-mastery"}, {"title": "Claude Code hooks explained: the missing layer between prompts and production", "url": "https://joseparreogarcia.substack.com/p/claude-code-hooks-explained-the-missing"}, {"title": "GitHub - karanb192/claude-code-hooks: 🪝 A growing collection of useful Claude Code hooks. Copy, paste, customize.", "url": "https://github.com/karanb192/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks Complete Guide — Automate and Enforce Rules Reliably - SmartScope", "url": "https://smartscope.blog/en/generative-ai/claude/claude-code-hooks-guide/"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Automate Your AI Coding Workflow", "url": "https://www.ksred.com/claude-code-hooks-a-complete-guide-to-automating-your-ai-coding-workflow/"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: Complete Guide to All 12 Lifecycle Events", "url": "https://claudefa.st/blog/tools/hooks/hooks-guide"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks (2026): Block Claude Reading .env + 30 Hook Events, JSON Input, Exit Codes", "url": "https://www.morphllm.com/claude-code-hooks"}, {"title": "Claude Code Hooks: The Feature You’re Ignoring While Babysitting Your AI | by Lakshmi Narasimhan | Medium", "url": "https://medium.com/@lakshminp/claude-code-hooks-the-feature-youre-ignoring-while-babysitting-your-ai-789d39b46f6c"}], "tool_use_id": "srvtoolu_01Xxa3Ljvh4sphMRbUZoWyQs"}, "Based on the search results, here's what Claude Code hooks are:\n\n## Overview\n\nHooks are user-defined shell commands that execute at specific points in Claude Code's lifecycle. They provide deterministic control over Claude Code's behavior, ensuring certain actions always happen rather than relying on the LLM to choose to run them.\n\n## Key Purpose\n\nUse hooks to enforce project rules, automate repetitive tasks, and integrate Claude Code with your existing tools. Hooks inject deterministic processing into Claude Code's lifecycle. Unlike prompt instructions, which are requests that Claude may interpret flexibly, hooks execute the same way every time.\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\nHooks let you run code at key points in Claude Code's lifecycle: format files after edits, block commands before they execute, send notifications when Claude needs input, inject context at session start, and more.\n\nSome practical examples include:\n- **Auto-formatting**: Every time Claude Code writes or edits a file, a PostToolUse hook can run your formatter automatically. No more reviewing diffs full of formatting inconsistencies, no more manually running gofmt or prettier after every change.\n- **Safety enforcement**: You set up a PreToolUse hook that inspects every bash command before it runs.\n- **Notifications**: A Stop or Notification hook can fire a desktop notification when Claude finishes or needs input. Nothing fancy - just osascript on macOS or notify-send on Linux.\n\n## How They Work\n\nA hook starts with an event, can optionally be narrowed with a matcher, receives structured input from Claude Code, and then executes one or more handlers. Exit code 2 is your power tool. A PreToolUse hook that exits 2 stops the tool. A Stop hook that exits 2 forces Claude to keep working."], "searchCount": 1}, "tool_use_id": "toolu_0135CR6Nu93YubprSgspqiPh", "transcript_path": "<TRANSCRIPT_PATH>"}
